Yesterday: I dug into the bug in our network intelligence ETL where a lot of the domain names were showing up as NULL.

The Findings: I found an architectural mismatch in our join logic. Route 53 logs the EC2 instance's private IP, but the VPC Flow Logs capture the NAT Gateway's IP for outbound internet traffic. Because those source IPs didn't match, the join was failing and dropping the domains.

The Fix/Today: I updated the PySpark script to drop the source IP from the join entirely. We now map DNS resolution at the VPC level using just the destination IP, Account ID, and VPC ID. The pipeline is running smoothly now, and the missing domains are successfully populating.
